CHIKUNGUNYA (24): INDIA (KARNATAKA)
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Wed 25 Jun 2008
Source: Times of India [edited]
<http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Cities/Chikungunya_outbreak_in_Bangalore/articleshow/3161887.cms>


[It is official that] a chikungunya outbreak has hit the city
[Bangalore]. Of 21 samples sent to the Public Health Institute, 7 --
all from Srirampura and surrounding areas -- tested positive for
chikungunya, confirmed Dr H M Vinutha, joint director, PHI.

Dr Gangalakshmi, medical superintendent at BBMP [Bruhat Bengaluru
Mahanagara Palike] Referral Hospital, Srirampura, said 17 new cases
of chikungunya were treated on Tuesday [24 Jun 2008]. The disease was
first reported at the hospital, where 86 cases were treated on Sunday
[22 Jun 2008]. [All] 17 patients complained of high fever and joint
pain.

Chikungunya cases were reported in Malleswaram, Srirampura,
Rajajinagar, and Bhashyamnagar area and samples were sent to PHI.

Dr Gayathri, BBMP chief medical health officer, said the cases were
coming down in referral hospitals, but still being reported at
private clinics and hospitals in the city.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett

[Chikungunya outbreaks continue to pop up in India. This one in
Karnataka has been laboratory confirmed.

A map of India showing the location of Bangalore in Karnataka can be
accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_pol01.jpg>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of India can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=22.9,79.6,5>. - Mod.TY]
